{% import "macros.j2" as macros -%}
You are an expert customer support classifier performing intent detection.

Project: {{ project.name }}
Task variant: {{ task.name }}
Task mode: {{ task.mode }}
Request ID: {{ request.id }}
Customer: {{ request.customer_name }}
Product: {{ request.product_type }}
Language: {{ request.language }}
Urgency: {{ request.urgency_level }}

Text:
"{{ request.text }}"

Allowed intent labels: {{ macros.comma_list(task.labels) }}

{% if task.mode == "document" -%}
Classify the primary intent of this support request.
{% elif task.mode == "category" -%}
Classify intent separately for each category:
{% for category in request.categories -%}
- {{ category }}
{% endfor -%}
Use `not_applicable` only if the request does not contain enough information about that category.
{% endif %}

{% if request.contains_sarcasm -%}
Important: this request may contain sarcasm. Interpret the intended intent, not only the literal wording.
{% endif -%}

{% if request.has_attachments -%}
Note: The customer has attached error logs or additional files.
{% endif -%}

{% if task.include_few_shot -%}
Examples:
{% for example in examples[:task.max_examples] %}
Input: "{{ example.text }}"
Output:
{
  "intent": "{{ example.intent }}",
  "reason": "{{ example.reason }}"
}
{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}

Return {% if task.json_only %}only valid JSON{% else %}a concise structured answer{% endif %}.

{% if task.mode == "document" -%}
Required JSON schema:
{
  "request_id": "{{ request.id }}",
  "intent": "one of: {{ task.labels | join(', ') }}",
  "confidence": "number between 0 and 1"{% if task.include_reasoning_field %},
  "reason": "one short sentence explaining the decision"{% endif %}
}
{% elif task.mode == "category" -%}
Required JSON schema:
{
  "request_id": "{{ request.id }}",
  "category_intents": [
    {% for category in request.categories -%}
    {
      "category": "{{ category }}",
      "intent": "one of: {{ task.labels | join(', ') }}",
      "evidence": "short phrase from the request"
    }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
    {% endfor -%}
  ]
}
{% endif -%}
